<p><b>  Technical guidance on the application of a human rights-
based approach to the implementation of policies and 
programmes to reduce preventable maternal morbidity and 
mortality 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for 
</b></p>
<p><b>Human Rights 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i></p>
<p> The present report contains concise technical guidance, in accordance with the 
request made by the Human Rights Council in its resolution 18/2. The aim of the report is 
to assist policymakers in improving women&#8217;s health and rights by providing guidance on 
</p>
<p>implementing policies and programmes to reduce maternal mortality and morbidity in 
accordance with human rights standards. It highlights the human rights implications for 
multiple actors in the policymaking, implementation and review cycle, as well as the need 
for robust enforcement mechanisms and international assistance and cooperation. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b> </b>United Nations A/HRC/21/22 
</p>
<p> 
</p>

