<p>90. <b>The design, implementation and evaluation of all aspects of international 
assistance and cooperation should ensure the participation of civil society and the 
</b></p>
<p><b>intended beneficiaries of programmes</b>. Development partners should make their 
programme evaluations public and report regularly, in accessible formats, to civil society 
groups, national parliaments and other national and United Nations oversight bodies.  
</p>
